too much to drink ranged from 83 percent in wisconsin to 13 
percent in kentucky 
in maryland 568 percent of those surveyed had had a 
cholesterol check while in new mexico it was just 293 
in new hampshire 575 percent of the women surveyed had had a 
mammogram compared with 346 percent in nebraska 
and while 413 percent of those 65 and older in montana had 
gotten their flu shots for the year just 24 percent of those in 
