people languish in local camps 
overseas resettlement of boat people has slowed down leading to 
a hong kong government decision to seek the repatriation of all 
vietnamese who fled their homeland for economic reasons 
hong kong is almost at the end of its tether and desperate to 
find a solution for this crisis wu wrote in his letter the 
cardinal asked for help in offering the vietnamese permanent homes 
as soon as possible in other countries 
nearly 270000 people in hong kong are roman catholic or about 5 
