the remainder of the year because of high interest rates 
the commerce department reported that sales fell to a seasonally 
adjusted 1408 billion last month after dropping 01 percent in 
may it was the first backtoback monthly decline since 1987 when 
sales declined 08 percent in september and 09 percent in october 
retail spending is watched closly as a measure of the overall 
economy since it accounts for about a third of economic activity 
car sales which represent about 20 percent of total retail 
sales led the overall decline last month they fell 20 percent 
following a 18 percent drop in may it was the steepest fall since 
a 40 percent decline in october 1987 
