<TEXT>
janos kadar who led the communist party 
for 32 years until losing power to a new generation of reformers 
was buried friday and praised as an early advocate of change 
thousands of people attended the somber state ceremony which 
culminated two days of emotional tribute to the 77yearold leader 
who died july 6 14 months after his ouster 
his great merit was to become a reformer in an age of 
rigidity said president bruno f straub referring to kadars 
