the communist party recently reevaluated the uprising as a 
popular revolt and nagy was rehabilitated his remains were 
reburied in an elaborate ceremony june 16 that was attended by 
hundreds of thousands of hungarians 
only hours after kadars death the hungarian supreme court 
declared nagy innocent of all charges 
