a spokesman for aouns command speaking on condition of 
anonymity said a syrian gunboat intercepted the latest tanker in 
lebanese territorial waters early in the day searched it for 
weapons and ammunition and allowed the captain to resume his 
voyage 
i dont understand why syrian gunners shelled the ship after 
the syrian gunboat permitted it to continue said the spokesman 
who refused to give any details about the tanker and its cargo 
citing security considerations 
he said the syrians shelled the christian coast from positions in 
moslem west beirut and the northern town of salaata on the edge of 
the 310squaremile enclave 
he said aouns gunners scored several direct hits on syrian 
artillery emplacements in beirut and the north however the claim 
could not be independently verified 
shells exploded near the american university of beirut in the 
citys moslem sector witnesses said 
the syrian military headquarters in beirut refused to comment 
a police spokesman who cannot be named in line with standing 
rules said syrian barrage concentrated on the 28mile christian 
stretch of lebanons 130mile mediterranean coast 
the syrians have besieged the christian enclave since march 12 in 
retaliation for a blockade aoun ordered of illegal ports run by 
syrianbacked militias south of beirut that he said were depriving 
his government of 100 million a year in tax revenue 
the syrian navy joined the blockade earlier this month after 
syria claimed aoun obtained sovietdesigned frog7 missiles from its 
traditional arab rival iraq the missiles are capable of hitting 
damascus the syrian capital 
aoun and his aides have refused to confirm or deny that they have 
frog7 missiles but iraq said thursday that aoun has the missiles 
which have a range of more than 40 miles 
an editorial in the official daily newspaper althawra 
