recent liberalization of policies will help 
align the beef industries in a number of pacific rim countries that 
share trading interests with the united states an agriculture 
department report said friday 
other affected countries include canada australia new zealand 
south korea and taiwan according to a report by the departments 
economic research service 
the trade flows resulting from liberalization will be directly 
influenced by underlying patterns in beef production and consumption 
in these countries the report said 
a decline in cattle inventories during the decade 197686 in 
north america and oceania appears to be ending although per capita 
beef consumption may not rebound to earlier levels the report 
said 
continued growth in beef consumption and market access in east 
asia will become even more important to the beefexporting 
countries 
the report said diets of east asians are shifting rapidly to more 
meats dairy products caloric sweeteners and fats and oils but 
less grain 
in contrast diets in north america and oceania are shifting to 
more grains and less beef the report said 
