the expected improved results are being attributed to a steady 
decline in shortterm interest rates that has prompted some 
investors to transfer money from money market funds and bank 
certificates of deposit to investments with higher returns 
generating more trading profit for the firms 
for instance the treasurys oneyear bill had a yield of 810 
percent at the end of june compared with 958 percent at the end of 
