west german chancellor helmut kohl a day after talks with canadian 
prime minister brian mulroney 
mexico the united states southern neighbor has often led 
efforts to bring an end to the third world debt crisis which dates 
to 1982 when that country was unable to meet its loan payments 
kohl met informally with salinas and sarney to discuss debt 
rescheduling and the german leaders ideas for debt for nature 
swaps according to german government spokesman hans klein under a 
swap arrangement some foreign loans would be forgiven in exchange 
for promises of environmental protection 
at the economic summit uno plans to pledge nearly 40 billion 
for debt relief and environmental aid for developing nations 
according to a foreign ministry official who earlier in the week 
briefed reporters in tokyo on condition of anonymity 
he wants to increase japans recycling of funds program for 
the debtor nations by 35 billion which will include 55 billion 
for the brady plan 
the recycling of money refers to the governments effort to use 
capital from its trade surplus to help poorer nations 
in addition 225 billion will be set aside for projects to 
preserve the environment and study environmental problems 
