<TEXT>
british brewer guinness plc will pay an extra 85 
million pounds or 138 million to former distillers co 
shareholders to settle a dispute stemming from its takeover of the 
liquor company the panel on takeovers and mergers said friday 
guinness acquired distillers for 253 billion pounds or 41 
billion in 1986 
the takeover panel a selfregulatory body which oversees bids 
involving british companies said guinness would pay the difference 
between its official 6303pence a share or 1021 offer to 
distillers shareholders and the 731 pence per share which guinness 
paid separately for shares through a swiss company acting on its 
behalf 
the purchases made at the higher price were found by the takeover 
panel to be in breach of british regulations they and a number of 
other alleged irregularities have become known as the guinness 
affair seven men involved in the takeover including 
thenchairman ernest saunders face trial on criminal charges 
related to the case 
the payments to shareholders are in the best interests of the 
company and its shareholders guinness chairman anthony tennant 
said 
the panel said that distillers shareholders who had accepted 
guinness cash offer would be paid another 1007 pence a share plus 
interest charges of 10 percent a year 
compensation also will be paid to distillers shareholders who 
acquired guinness shares in accepting guinness alternative 
cashandshares offer and sold them prior to the official completion 
of the bid 
distillers shareholders who didnt accept either offer yet sold 
their distillers shares for less than 731 pence before the official 
completion of the bid would also be compensated the panel said 
the panel said guinness estimated the cost of the compensation 
could total as much as 85 million pounds 
</TEXT>
