<DOCNO> AP890714-0257 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
as if junk bonds werent enough for investors to 
worry about now the spotlight has been turned on yet another 
highrisk highyield security junk commercial paper 
the perils of this form of corporate debt were pointed out 
recently by the collapse of integrated resources inc a real estate 
and investment company that defaulted on 955 million in shortterm 
obligations including its commercial paper 
complicating matters is that integrated resources commercial 
paper was not rated as junk or highrisk until after the companys 
financial problems came to light last month that means investors 
saw their investmentgrade integrated resources commercial paper 
turn into junk in a matter of days 
however most small investors have little to worry about their 
only exposure to commercial paper would be through mutual funds and 
pension funds and the risk to these investments is small experts 
say 
one type of mutual fund moneymarket funds invest in large 
amounts of investmentgrade commercial paper but most are barred by 
federal law from purchasing lowrated commercial paper 
the major mutual fund operators do their own credit analysis 
before they make any investment said michael lipper president of 
lipper analytical services inc which tracks the mutualfund 
industry 
that kind of examination keeps integrated resources paper out of 
the portfolios of most of the largest fund operators including 
fidelity investments the vanguard group inc kemper financial 
companies inc and t rowe price associates inc 
these fund operators said integrated resources never met their 
investment standards despite its acceptable ratings from the credit 
rating agencies 
we wouldnt have even considered it said steven norwitz a 
price vice president it had been in a negative cashflow 
situation for years 
one exception is value line inc a mutual fund operator that 
held integrated resources paper in one of its money market funds 
value line said the investment represented about 38 percent of 
the funds net assets market professionals have placed the amount 
at 22 million to 24 million value line would not reveal the 
figure 
value line said last week that it had bought the paper from the 
fund which eliminated it as a risk to the funds investors 
lipper said he believes other funds had invested in integrated 
resources paper but value line has been the only one to publicly 
acknowledge it 
fidelity vanguard and price among others also said they never 
invest in junk commercial paper for any of their mutual funds 
junk commercial paper is a small subset of the 450 billion 
commercial paper market used by companies to raise cash for 
shortterm needs 
commercial paper with investmentgrade ratings is considered a 
relatively safe investment companies issuing it usually have high 
ratings on all their debt obligations due to their strong financial 
positions 
commercial paper is a form of shortterm corporate iou usually 
not secured by assets though it is supposed to be backed by bank 
lines of credit companies sell the paper to raise money for periods 
ranging from a few days to a few months 
the reasons for issuing commercial paper vary some companies use 
it to tide them over until proceeds from a bond issue arrive others 
use it for working capital or to provide cash until funds from 
regular operations come in 
companies find commercial paper attractive because the interest 
rates they must pay on it usually are lower than bankloan rates 
commercial paper also provides flexibility in the length of the loan 
junk commercial paper by contrast is issued by companies that 
are deep in debt or have low debt ratings for other reasons its 
yield is higher than investmentgrade paper because of the added 
risk to investors 
the safety of the investmentgrade commercial paper market is 
reflected by its history only one issue has defaulted since the 
early 1970s said tom mcquire an executive vice president at 
moodys investors service that issue was manville corp which 
filed for bankruptcycourt protection over asbestosrelated lawsuits 
mcquire said he did not have figures on the number of junkpaper 
issues that have defaulted 
but while the track record of investmentgrade paper is 
excellent the integrated resources case shows it is not a foolproof 
place to put money 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
