eastern airlines on friday requested to use 100 
million from a courtmonitored escrow account toward its rebuilding 
program and union leaders said it was a sign the carrier is 
struggling in the 4monthold strike 
a spokesman for the miamibased carrier contends it was well 
documented that eastern could use some profits from the sale of 
planes and other assets in its reorganization into a smaller company 
eastern filed papers in us bankruptcy court in new york seeking 
to free the 100 million to pay off expenses 
eastern spokesman robin matell said he does not know when a 
ruling may be issued 
it was known from the beginning that we could use some of the 
proceeds from our asset transactions for rebuilding said matell 
i dont see why anyone is shocked by this 
but the air line pilots association on friday said easterns 
request for the funds suggests cashflow problems in operating a 
smaller carrier 
